🎯 1. OBSERVATION MODEL (A matrix) - PyMDP obj_array format
======================================================================
Matrix shape: (3, 3)
Interpretation: P(observation | state)
Each COLUMN represents a state, each ROW represents an observation
Each column should sum to 1.0 (probability distribution)

Full A Matrix:
         Left   Center  Right
See Left   0.900   0.050   0.050
See Center 0.050   0.900   0.050
See Right  0.050   0.050   0.900

Column sums (should be 1.0):
  Left: 1.000000
  Center: 1.000000
  Right: 1.000000

Observation Discriminability (using PyMDP entropy):
  See Left: entropy = 0.3944 (0=perfect, higher=ambiguous)
  See Center: entropy = 0.3944 (0=perfect, higher=ambiguous)
  See Right: entropy = 0.3944 (0=perfect, higher=ambiguous)

🚀 2. TRANSITION MODEL (B matrices) - PyMDP obj_array format
======================================================================
Matrix shape: (3, 3, 2)
Interpretation: P(next_state | current_state, action)
Dimensions: [next_state, current_state, action]
Each B[:,:,action] matrix should have columns summing to 1.0

Move Left (B[:,:,0]):
Current→Next   Left   Center  Right
Left         1.000   0.000   0.000
Center       0.950   0.050   0.000
Right        0.000   0.950   0.050
Column sums for Move Left:
