============================================================
VFE-BASED STATE INFERENCE DEMONSTRATION
============================================================
🧠 BAYESIAN STATE INFERENCE WITH VFE ANALYSIS
Following PyMDP free_energy_calculation.ipynb patterns

Starting with uniform beliefs (prior):
Initial beliefs: [0.33333333 0.33333333 0.33333333]

Sequential VFE-based observations:
Obs  | Prior        → Posterior     | VFE    | Surprise | Most Likely
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1   | [0.33333333 0.33333333 0.33333333] → [0.05 0.05 0.9 ] |  2.032 |    1.099 | Right (0.900)
 2   | [0.05 0.05 0.9 ] → [0.00306748 0.00306748 0.99386503] |  0.394 |    0.205 | Right (0.994)
 3   | [0.00306748 0.00306748 0.99386503] → [0.00291545 0.05247813 0.94460641] |  2.987 |    2.945 | Right (0.945)
 4   | [0.00291545 0.05247813 0.94460641] → [0.05 0.05 0.9 ] |  2.987 |    2.947 | Right (0.900)

🔬 VFE ANALYSIS SUMMARY
==================================================
Observation → VFE interpretation:
  Step 1 (Right ): VFE=2.032, Surprise=1.099 (High), P(o)=0.3333
  Step 2 (Right ): VFE=0.394, Surprise=0.205 (Low), P(o)=0.8150
  Step 3 (Center): VFE=2.987, Surprise=2.945 (High), P(o)=0.0526
  Step 4 (Left  ): VFE=2.987, Surprise=2.947 (High), P(o)=0.0525

📊 KEY VFE INSIGHTS:
• VFE = E_q[ln q(s) - ln p(o,s)] measures model fit
• Lower VFE = better model explanation of observations
• Surprise = -ln P(o) quantifies unexpectedness
• Sequential updates minimize VFE at each step
• PyMDP utilities ensure proper probability distributions

============================================================
EFE-BASED ACTION SELECTION DEMONSTRATION
============================================================
🎯 EXPECTED FREE ENERGY (EFE) FOR POLICY INFERENCE
Following PyMDP control module patterns
EFE = -Expected_Utility + Epistemic_Value
Lower EFE = more preferred action


